{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":504,"text":"I need to start by telling you a little bit"},{"time":3066,"text":"about my social life,"},{"time":4555,"text":"which I know may not seem relevant,"},{"time":7473,"text":"but it is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":9220,"text":"When people meet me at parties"},{"time":11150,"text":"and they find out that I'm an English professor"},{"time":13342,"text":"who specializes in language,"},{"time":15739,"text":"they generally have one of two reactions."},{"time":19189,"text":"One set of people look frightened. (Laughter)"},{"time":24378,"text":"They often say something like,"},{"time":25971,"text":"\"Oh, I'd better be careful what I say."},{"time":29277,"text":"I'm sure you'll hear every mistake I make.\""},{"time":32495,"text":"And then they stop talking. (Laughter)"},{"time":36553,"text":"And they wait for me to go away"},{"time":38950,"text":"and talk to someone else."},{"time":41187,"text":"The other set of people,"},{"time":43222,"text":"their eyes light up,"},{"time":45647,"text":"and they say,"},{"time":46878,"text":"\"You are just the person I want to talk to.\""},{"time":51187,"text":"And then they tell me about whatever it is"},{"time":53607,"text":"they think is going wrong with the English language."},{"time":56142,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":58511,"text":"A couple of weeks ago, I was at a dinner party"},{"time":60828,"text":"and the man to my right"},{"time":63065,"text":"started telling me about all the ways"},{"time":65100,"text":"that the Internet is degrading the English language."},{"time":68381,"text":"He brought up Facebook, and he said,"},{"time":71620,"text":"\"To defriend? I mean, is that even a real word?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":77470,"text":"I want to pause on that question:"},{"time":81040,"text":"What makes a word real?"},{"time":84826,"text":"My dinner companion and I both know"},{"time":86910,"text":"what the verb \"defriend\" means,"},{"time":90077,"text":"so when does a new word like \"defriend\""},{"time":92777,"text":"become real?"},{"time":94858,"text":"Who has the authority to make those kinds"},{"time":97362,"text":"of official decisions about words, anyway?"},{"time":100780,"text":"Those are the questions I want to talk about today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":105075,"text":"I think most people, when they say a word isn't real,"},{"time":108375,"text":"what they mean is, it doesn't appear"},{"time":110236,"text":"in a standard dictionary."},{"time":111864,"text":"That, of course, raises a host of other questions,"},{"time":114327,"text":"including, who writes dictionaries?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":119724,"text":"Before I go any further,"},{"time":121048,"text":"let me clarify my role in all of this."},{"time":123490,"text":"I do not write dictionaries."},{"time":125998,"text":"I do, however, collect new words"},{"time":128695,"text":"much the way dictionary editors do,"},{"time":131750,"text":"and the great thing about being a historian"},{"time":133573,"text":"of the English language"},{"time":134640,"text":"is that I get to call this \"research.\""},{"time":138276,"text":"When I teach the history of the English language,"},{"time":140620,"text":"I require that students teach me"},{"time":143377,"text":"two new slang words before I will begin class."},{"time":146903,"text":"Over the years, I have learned"},{"time":149220,"text":"some great new slang this way,"},{"time":152454,"text":"including \"hangry,\" which --"},{"time":156492,"text":"(Applause) â€”"},{"time":160188,"text":"which is when you are cranky or angry"},{"time":162535,"text":"because you are hungry,"},{"time":166774,"text":"and \"adorkable,\""},{"time":171550,"text":"which is when you are adorable"},{"time":173257,"text":"in kind of a dorky way,"},{"time":176278,"text":"clearly, terrific words that fill"},{"time":179471,"text":"important gaps in the English language."},{"time":182176,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":186389,"text":"But how real are they"},{"time":189060,"text":"if we use them primarily as slang"},{"time":191279,"text":"and they don't yet appear in a dictionary?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":195396,"text":"With that, let's turn to dictionaries."},{"time":198213,"text":"I'm going to do this as a show of hands:"},{"time":200053,"text":"How many of you still regularly"},{"time":202387,"text":"refer to a dictionary, either print or online?"},{"time":207338,"text":"Okay, so that looks like most of you."},{"time":209532,"text":"Now, a second question. Again, a show of hands:"},{"time":212697,"text":"How many of you have ever looked to see"},{"time":215902,"text":"who edited the dictionary you are using?"},{"time":222048,"text":"Okay, many fewer."},{"time":225680,"text":"At some level, we know that there are human hands"},{"time":229360,"text":"behind dictionaries,"},{"time":230936,"text":"but we're really not sure who those hands belong to."},{"time":235207,"text":"I'm actually fascinated by this."},{"time":237547,"text":"Even the most critical people out there"},{"time":240020,"text":"tend not to be very critical about dictionaries,"},{"time":242614,"text":"not distinguishing among them"},{"time":244497,"text":"and not asking a whole lot of questions"},{"time":246568,"text":"about who edited them."},{"time":248791,"text":"Just think about the phrase"},{"time":250414,"text":"\"Look it up in the dictionary,\""},{"time":252890,"text":"which suggests that all dictionaries"},{"time":254567,"text":"are exactly the same."},{"time":256273,"text":"Consider the library here on campus,"},{"time":258873,"text":"where you go into the reading room,"},{"time":260569,"text":"and there is a large, unabridged dictionary"},{"time":263442,"text":"up on a pedestal in this place of honor and respect"},{"time":267320,"text":"lying open so we can go stand before it"},{"time":269667,"text":"to get answers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":271870,"text":"Now, don't get me wrong,"},{"time":274176,"text":"dictionaries are fantastic resources,"},{"time":277381,"text":"but they are human"},{"time":278930,"text":"and they are not timeless."},{"time":281211,"text":"I'm struck as a teacher"},{"time":283013,"text":"that we tell students to critically question"},{"time":286230,"text":"every text they read, every website they visit,"},{"time":289964,"text":"except dictionaries,"},{"time":291452,"text":"which we tend to treat as un-authored,"},{"time":294617,"text":"as if they came from nowhere to give us answers"},{"time":297259,"text":"about what words really mean."},{"time":301603,"text":"Here's the thing: If you ask dictionary editors,"},{"time":305200,"text":"what they'll tell you"},{"time":306358,"text":"is they're just trying to keep up with us"},{"time":308672,"text":"as we change the language."},{"time":310427,"text":"They're watching what we say and what we write"},{"time":312912,"text":"and trying to figure out what's going to stick"},{"time":315070,"text":"and what's not going to stick."},{"time":317220,"text":"They have to gamble,"},{"time":318537,"text":"because they want to appear cutting edge"},{"time":320286,"text":"and catch the words that are going to make it,"},{"time":322942,"text":"such as LOL,"},{"time":325381,"text":"but they don't want to appear faddish"},{"time":327585,"text":"and include the words that aren't going to make it,"},{"time":330127,"text":"and I think a word that they're watching right now"},{"time":331940,"text":"is YOLO, you only live once."}]},{"cues":[{"time":337317,"text":"Now I get to hang out with dictionary editors,"},{"time":339811,"text":"and you might be surprised"},{"time":341319,"text":"by one of the places where we hang out."},{"time":343535,"text":"Every January, we go"},{"time":345672,"text":"to the American Dialect Society annual meeting,"},{"time":348825,"text":"where among other things,"},{"time":350172,"text":"we vote on the word of the year."},{"time":353930,"text":"There are about 200 or 300 people who come,"},{"time":356933,"text":"some of the best known\nlinguists in the United States."},{"time":359373,"text":"To give you a sense of the flavor of the meeting,"},{"time":361231,"text":"it occurs right before happy hour."},{"time":364532,"text":"Anyone who comes can vote."},{"time":366608,"text":"The most important rule is"},{"time":367920,"text":"that you can vote with only one hand."},{"time":371049,"text":"In the past, some of the winners have been"},{"time":374513,"text":"\"tweet\" in 2009"},{"time":376998,"text":"and \"hashtag\" in 2012."},{"time":380403,"text":"\"Chad\" was the word of the year in the year 2000,"},{"time":383462,"text":"because who knew what a chad was before 2000,"},{"time":387282,"text":"and \"WMD\" in 2002."}]},{"cues":[{"time":391696,"text":"Now, we have other categories in which we vote too,"},{"time":394497,"text":"and my favorite category"},{"time":396090,"text":"is most creative word of the year."},{"time":398474,"text":"Past winners in this category have included"},{"time":401224,"text":"\"recombobulation area,\""},{"time":404277,"text":"which is at the Milwaukee Airport after security,"},{"time":408080,"text":"where you can recombobulate."},{"time":410640,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":412124,"text":"You can put your belt back on,"},{"time":413643,"text":"put your computer back in your bag."},{"time":418289,"text":"And then my all-time favorite word at this vote,"},{"time":421621,"text":"which is \"multi-slacking.\""},{"time":423847,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":426350,"text":"And multi-slacking is the act"},{"time":428633,"text":"of having multiple windows up on your screen"},{"time":431501,"text":"so it looks like you're working"},{"time":432902,"text":"when you're actually goofing around on the web."},{"time":434996,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":441381,"text":"Will all of these words stick? Absolutely not."},{"time":444989,"text":"And we have made some questionable choices,"},{"time":447888,"text":"for example in 2006"},{"time":449565,"text":"when the word of the year was \"Plutoed,\""},{"time":451604,"text":"to mean demoted."},{"time":453596,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":458586,"text":"But some of the past winners"},{"time":460955,"text":"now seem completely unremarkable,"},{"time":463870,"text":"such as \"app\""},{"time":465388,"text":"and \"e\" as a prefix,"},{"time":467401,"text":"and \"google\" as a verb."}]},{"cues":[{"time":470360,"text":"Now, a few weeks before our vote,"},{"time":474427,"text":"Lake Superior State University"},{"time":476208,"text":"issues its list of banished words for the year."},{"time":480987,"text":"What is striking about this"},{"time":482920,"text":"is that there's actually often quite a lot of overlap"},{"time":485691,"text":"between their list and the list that we are considering"},{"time":488528,"text":"for words of the year,"},{"time":490778,"text":"and this is because we're noticing the same thing."},{"time":494870,"text":"We're noticing words that are coming into prominence."},{"time":497900,"text":"It's really a question of attitude."},{"time":500053,"text":"Are you bothered by language\nfads and language change,"},{"time":503720,"text":"or do you find it fun, interesting,"},{"time":507130,"text":"something worthy of study"},{"time":508484,"text":"as part of a living language?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":511369,"text":"The list by Lake Superior State University"},{"time":513525,"text":"continues a fairly long tradition in English"},{"time":516170,"text":"of complaints about new words."},{"time":518443,"text":"So here is Dean Henry Alford in 1875,"},{"time":522795,"text":"who was very concerned that \"desirability\""},{"time":525041,"text":"is really a terrible word."},{"time":527490,"text":"In 1760, Benjamin Franklin"},{"time":530224,"text":"wrote a letter to David Hume"},{"time":531680,"text":"giving up the word \"colonize\" as bad."}]},{"cues":[{"time":535483,"text":"Over the years, we've also seen worries"},{"time":537682,"text":"about new pronunciations."},{"time":539572,"text":"Here is Samuel Rogers in 1855"},{"time":542620,"text":"who is concerned about some\nfashionable pronunciations"},{"time":545219,"text":"that he finds offensive,"},{"time":547226,"text":"and he says \"as if contemplate were not bad enough,"},{"time":550714,"text":"balcony makes me sick.\""},{"time":553132,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":556528,"text":"The word is borrowed in from Italian"},{"time":558878,"text":"and it was pronounced bal-COE-nee."}]},{"cues":[{"time":562418,"text":"These complaints now strike us as quaint,"},{"time":565361,"text":"if not downright adorkable -- (Laughter) --"},{"time":570306,"text":"but here's the thing:"},{"time":573040,"text":"we still get quite worked up about language change."},{"time":577413,"text":"I have an entire file in my office"},{"time":579475,"text":"of newspaper articles"},{"time":582537,"text":"which express concern about illegitimate words"},{"time":585230,"text":"that should not have been included in the dictionary,"},{"time":587109,"text":"including \"LOL\""},{"time":588557,"text":"when it got into the Oxford English Dictionary"},{"time":590627,"text":"and \"defriend\""},{"time":592402,"text":"when it got into the Oxford American Dictionary."},{"time":595174,"text":"I also have articles expressing concern"},{"time":597391,"text":"about \"invite\" as a noun,"},{"time":600260,"text":"\"impact\" as a verb,"},{"time":602216,"text":"because only teeth can be impacted,"},{"time":605187,"text":"and \"incentivize\" is described"},{"time":608162,"text":"as \"boorish, bureaucratic misspeak.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":612673,"text":"Now, it's not that dictionary editors"},{"time":614634,"text":"ignore these kinds of attitudes about language."},{"time":617325,"text":"They try to provide us some guidance about words"},{"time":619880,"text":"that are considered slang or informal"},{"time":622150,"text":"or offensive, often through usage labels,"},{"time":625293,"text":"but they're in something of a bind,"},{"time":626983,"text":"because they're trying to describe what we do,"},{"time":630635,"text":"and they know that we often go to dictionaries"},{"time":632964,"text":"to get information about how we should use a word"},{"time":635732,"text":"well or appropriately."},{"time":637640,"text":"In response, the American Heritage Dictionaries"},{"time":640664,"text":"include usage notes."},{"time":642805,"text":"Usage notes tend to occur with words"},{"time":644922,"text":"that are troublesome in one way,"},{"time":646245,"text":"and one of the ways that they can be troublesome"},{"time":649110,"text":"is that they're changing meaning."},{"time":651043,"text":"Now usage notes involve very human decisions,"},{"time":654469,"text":"and I think, as dictionary users,"},{"time":656528,"text":"we're often not as aware of those human decisions"},{"time":658770,"text":"as we should be."},{"time":659869,"text":"To show you what I mean,"},{"time":660993,"text":"we'll look at an example, but before we do,"},{"time":663710,"text":"I want to explain what the dictionary editors"},{"time":665692,"text":"are trying to deal with in this usage note."}]},{"cues":[{"time":668990,"text":"Think about the word \"peruse\""},{"time":671664,"text":"and how you use that word."},{"time":675302,"text":"I would guess many of you are thinking"},{"time":677838,"text":"of skim, scan, reading quickly."},{"time":682375,"text":"Some of you may even have some walking involved,"},{"time":685210,"text":"because you're perusing grocery store shelves,"},{"time":687456,"text":"or something like that."},{"time":689127,"text":"You might be surprised to learn"},{"time":691611,"text":"that if you look in most standard dictionaries,"},{"time":693480,"text":"the first definition will be to read carefully,"},{"time":696253,"text":"or pore over."},{"time":698697,"text":"American Heritage has that as the first definition."},{"time":701556,"text":"They then have, as the second definition, skim,"},{"time":704521,"text":"and next to that, they say \"usage problem.\""},{"time":708316,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":710226,"text":"And then they include a usage note,"},{"time":712314,"text":"which is worth looking at."}]},{"cues":[{"time":714191,"text":"So here's the usage note:"},{"time":716102,"text":"\"Peruse has long meant 'to read thoroughly'..."},{"time":718459,"text":"But the word is often used more loosely,"},{"time":720226,"text":"to mean simply 'to read.'..."},{"time":722386,"text":"Further extension of the word\nto mean 'to glance over, skim,'"},{"time":725315,"text":"has traditionally been considered an error,"},{"time":727771,"text":"but our ballot results suggest that it is becoming"},{"time":730174,"text":"somewhat more acceptable."},{"time":731870,"text":"When asked about the sentence,"},{"time":733269,"text":"'I only had a moment to peruse the manual quickly,'"},{"time":736000,"text":"66 percent of the [Usage] Panel"},{"time":738075,"text":"found it unacceptable in 1988,"},{"time":740422,"text":"58 percent in 1999,"},{"time":742529,"text":"and 48 percent in 2011.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":746397,"text":"Ah, the Usage Panel,"},{"time":748358,"text":"that trusted body of language authorities"},{"time":750968,"text":"who is getting more lenient about this."},{"time":753820,"text":"Now, what I hope you're thinking right now is,"},{"time":755890,"text":"\"Wait, who's on the Usage Panel?"},{"time":759885,"text":"And what should I do with their pronouncements?\""},{"time":762997,"text":"If you look in the front matter"},{"time":764960,"text":"of American Heritage Dictionaries,"},{"time":766068,"text":"you can actually find the names"},{"time":767643,"text":"of the people on the Usage Panel."},{"time":769212,"text":"But who looks at the front matter of dictionaries?"},{"time":771244,"text":"There are about 200 people on the Usage Panel."},{"time":774291,"text":"They include academicians,"},{"time":776668,"text":"journalists, creative writers."},{"time":778345,"text":"There's a Supreme Court justice on it"},{"time":780437,"text":"and a few linguists."},{"time":782336,"text":"As of 2005, the list includes me."},{"time":787168,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":791342,"text":"Here's what we can do for you."},{"time":794710,"text":"We can give you a sense"},{"time":797070,"text":"of the range of opinions about contested usage."},{"time":800122,"text":"That is and should be the extent of our authority."},{"time":803479,"text":"We are not a language academy."},{"time":806890,"text":"About once a year, I get a ballot"},{"time":809837,"text":"that asks me about whether new uses,"},{"time":812869,"text":"new pronunciations, new meanings, are acceptable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":816207,"text":"Now here's what I do to fill out the ballot."},{"time":819099,"text":"I listen to what other people are saying and writing."},{"time":822607,"text":"I do not listen to my own likes"},{"time":824851,"text":"and dislikes about the English language."},{"time":828060,"text":"I will be honest with you:"},{"time":829529,"text":"I do not like the word \"impactful,\""},{"time":832478,"text":"but that is neither here nor there"},{"time":834480,"text":"in terms of whether \"impactful\"\nis becoming common usage"},{"time":837719,"text":"and becoming more acceptable in written prose."},{"time":840970,"text":"So to be responsible,"},{"time":842018,"text":"what I do is go look at usage,"},{"time":844546,"text":"which often involves going to look"},{"time":846382,"text":"at online databases such as Google Books."},{"time":849077,"text":"Well, if you look for \"impactful\" in Google Books,"},{"time":851897,"text":"here is what you find."},{"time":855103,"text":"Well, it sure looks like \"impactful\""},{"time":857344,"text":"is proving useful"},{"time":859074,"text":"for a certain number of writers,"},{"time":860703,"text":"and has become more and more useful"},{"time":862303,"text":"over the last 20 years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":864262,"text":"Now, there are going to be changes"},{"time":866415,"text":"that all of us don't like in the language."},{"time":869049,"text":"There are going to be changes where you think,"},{"time":871233,"text":"\"Really?"},{"time":872220,"text":"Does the language have to change that way?\""},{"time":875905,"text":"What I'm saying is,"},{"time":877588,"text":"we should be less quick"},{"time":879310,"text":"to decide that that change is terrible,"},{"time":883101,"text":"we should be less quick to impose"},{"time":884815,"text":"our likes and dislikes about words on other people,"},{"time":888116,"text":"and we should be entirely reluctant"},{"time":891030,"text":"to think that the English language is in trouble."},{"time":893774,"text":"It's not. It is rich and vibrant and filled"},{"time":897970,"text":"with the creativity of the speakers who speak it."},{"time":900980,"text":"In retrospect, we think it's fascinating"},{"time":903598,"text":"that the word \"nice\" used to mean silly,"},{"time":906976,"text":"and that the word \"decimate\""},{"time":908660,"text":"used to mean to kill one in every 10."},{"time":912165,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":917162,"text":"We think that Ben Franklin was being silly"},{"time":922255,"text":"to worry about \"notice\" as a verb."},{"time":924904,"text":"Well, you know what?"},{"time":926367,"text":"We're going to look pretty silly in a hundred years"},{"time":929067,"text":"for worrying about \"impact\" as a verb"},{"time":931364,"text":"and \"invite\" as a noun."},{"time":934176,"text":"The language is not going to change so fast"},{"time":936416,"text":"that we can't keep up."},{"time":938313,"text":"Language just doesn't work that way."},{"time":940596,"text":"I hope that what you can do"},{"time":942209,"text":"is find language change not worrisome"},{"time":945038,"text":"but fun and fascinating,"},{"time":947076,"text":"just the way dictionary editors do."},{"time":950085,"text":"I hope you can enjoy being part"},{"time":952047,"text":"of the creativity that is continually remaking"},{"time":957051,"text":"our language and keeping it robust."}]},{"cues":[{"time":960327,"text":"So how does a word get into a dictionary?"},{"time":963247,"text":"It gets in because we use it"},{"time":965716,"text":"and we keep using it,"},{"time":967340,"text":"and dictionary editors are paying attention to us."},{"time":971575,"text":"If you're thinking, \"But that lets all of us decide"},{"time":974695,"text":"what words mean,\""},{"time":976444,"text":"I would say, \"Yes it does,"},{"time":980495,"text":"and it always has.\""},{"time":982847,"text":"Dictionaries are a wonderful guide and resource,"},{"time":986774,"text":"but there is no objective\ndictionary authority out there"},{"time":990270,"text":"that is the final arbiter about what words mean."},{"time":994043,"text":"If a community of speakers is using a word"},{"time":996556,"text":"and knows what it means, it's real."},{"time":1000152,"text":"That word might be slangy,"},{"time":1001520,"text":"that word might be informal,"},{"time":1003162,"text":"that word might be a word that you think"},{"time":1005067,"text":"is illogical or unnecessary,"},{"time":1007524,"text":"but that word that we're using,"},{"time":1010075,"text":"that word is real."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1012433,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1014774,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}